THERE is a standoff between foreign nationals and cops in Cape Town. Central Business District. Protesting foreign nationals at the UN High Commissioner for refugees, Office entrance say they are tired of being treated badly in South Africa. Hundreds of the foreign nationals chanted songs “We wanna go….. We wanna go”, demanding help from government to be transported back to their home countries. According to the protesters, they are being held hostage in South Africa, and want to go back home. The police were called to the scene after the refugees reportedly started being violent.  FOOTAGE COURTESY OF SABC NEWS.   